<strong style="font-size: 12px;">Summary</strong></p>
<p>
The Professional Services team has an opening for an experienced client facing Analytics Solutions Architect to assist clients with their analytics needs: building analytics based solutions using Revolution Analytics&rsquo; products, embedding analytics into existing products, and scaling clients&rsquo; analytics needs.</p>
<p>
<strong>Primary Responsibilities</strong><br />
The Analytics Solutions Architect is responsible for the technical requirements, design, and delivery of simple to large-scale solution architectures, and complex multi-tiered analytical-focused solutions.</p>
<p>
The ideal candidate is a seasoned professional with deep and broad experience in the IT, software, and consulting space who enjoys a very dynamic work experience with bleeding edge high performance technologies. Must thrive in the Start Up mindset where charting new territory is the norm.&nbsp; Problem solving, learning in the field, translating technical concepts for the business user, and leadership are critical to this position. Travel: Up to 70%</p>
<p>
The role has four core functions:</p>
<ol>
<li>
Pre-sales support of Sales and SE team to promote and position Revolution Analytic solutions as well as contribute to customer proposals</li>
<li>
Lead the development of technical architecture, requirements, and design and takes accountability of technical validity of the customer solution including installation and integration</li>
<li>
Act as co-lead with Project Manager for project team providing leadership, direction, coaching, technical assignments, and execution of the full software development lifecycle including documentation</li>
<li>
Drive field developed innovation and IP back into R&amp;D and works highly collaboratively with Technical Support, Sales, and Training</li>
<li>
Support onsite client project delivery</li>
<li>
Assist with RFI/RFP technical responses.</li>
<li>
Support R User Groups as requested.</li>
</ol>
<p>
A typical project team consists of a Project Manager, Solutions Architect, Data Scientist and/or R consultant.</p>
